== Vendored numerical libraries ==

QUADPACK
  Path:      libk26astro_quad/src/upstream/quadpack/
  Original:  R. Piessens, E. de Doncker-Kapenga, C. W. Überhuber,
             D. K. Kahaner (1983).
  Port:      Jacob Williams (2018-2024), modern Fortran rewrite.
  License:   BSD-3-Clause (modern port); SLATEC public domain
             (original algorithm).

ODEPACK (DLSODA)
  Path:      libk26astro_ode/src/upstream/odepack/
  Source:    Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory
             (Alan Hindmarsh et al., 1983);
             modern Fortran rewrite by Jacob Williams.
  License:   Public domain (US Government work, US DOE).

CMINPACK
  Path:      libk26astro_fit/src/upstream/cminpack/
  Source:    University of Chicago (2002);
             Frédéric Devernay (2007-2014), pure-C port of MINPACK 1
             (Moré, Garbow, Hillstrom 1980, Argonne National Lab).
  License:   Minpack Copyright Notice (1999), University of Chicago —
             a BSD-3-style license with a mandatory acknowledgment clause.
             The end-user documentation acknowledgment it requires:

               "This product includes software developed by the
                University of Chicago, as Operator of Argonne National
                Laboratory."

             Full text: libk26astro_fit/src/upstream/cminpack/LICENSE.

IGRF-14
  Path:      libk26astro_geomag/src/upstream/igrf/
  Source:    NOAA / National Centers for Environmental Information,
             with the British Geological Survey
             (Macmillan, Brown, Beggan).
  Coverage:  1900.0 to 2030.0 (definitive 1945.0 to 2020.0).
  License:   Public domain (US Government work).

NRLMSISE-00
  Path:      libk26astro_atmos/src/upstream/nrlmsise00/
  Source:    US Naval Research Laboratory
             (J. M. Picone, A. E. Hedin, D. P. Drob; A. C. Aikin).
  Reference: Picone et al. (2002), "NRLMSISE-00 empirical model of
             the atmosphere: Statistical comparisons and scientific
             issues", J. Geophys. Res. Space Physics, 2002JA009430.
  License:   Public domain (US Government work).

== Bundled ephemeris data ==

JPL DE441 (inner-planet subset)
  Path:      libk26astro_ephem/data/de441_inner.spk
  Source:    Jet Propulsion Laboratory; NAIF / Solar System Dynamics
             Group (NASA).
  Upstream:  https://naif.jpl.nasa.gov/pub/naif/generic_kernels/spk/planets/
  References:
    Folkner W. M., Park R. S. (2014), "The Planetary and Lunar
      Ephemerides DE430 and DE431", IPN Progress Report 42-196.
    Park R. S., Folkner W. M., Williams J. G., Boggs D. H. (2021),
      "The JPL Planetary and Lunar Ephemerides DE440 and DE441",
      The Astronomical Journal 161:105.
  License:   Public domain (US Government work).
  Full attribution: libk26astro_ephem/data/DE441_LICENSE.md.

== Astronomical reference tables ==

The following tabulated values are transcribed from open scientific
publications and ship inline within libk26astro_body. They are
reference data, not third-party source code; attribution is requested
in accordance with the publishing convention of each source.

IAU 2000A and IAU 2000B nutation series
  Path:      libk26astro_body/src/nutation_iau2000a.c
             libk26astro_body/src/nutation_iau2006_short.c
  Source:    IERS Conventions (2010), Chapter 5;
             McCarthy D. D., Luzum B. J. (2003).

IAU 2018 planetary and satellite rotation elements
  Path:      libk26astro_body/src/iau_rotations.c
  Source:    Archinal et al. (2018), "Report of the IAU Working Group
             on Cartographic Coordinates and Rotational Elements:
             2015", Celestial Mechanics and Dynamical Astronomy
             130:22; erratum 131:61 (2019).

Hipparcos-2 bright-star subset
  Path:      libk26astro_body/src/star_catalogue_hip.c
  Scope:     ~60 entries (naked-eye sky, V ≤ ~3).
  Source:    van Leeuwen F. (2007), "Hipparcos, the New Reduction of
             the Raw Data"; epoch J1991.25 TT.
             Catalogue distributed by the ESA / Hipparcos archive
             without restrictive licensing.
